#collect three marks from user
#calculate mark1 + mark2 + mark3 / 3

#if calculate > 90 ===> Grade A
#if calculate > 75 ==> Grade B
#calculate > 50  ==> grade C
#Other wise ===> Grade D

marks1 = input("Enter maths marks : ")
marks2 = input("Enter science marks : ")
marks3 = input("Enter english marks : ")

total = (int(marks1) + int(marks2) + int(marks3)) / 3
print(total)

if(total > 90):
    print("Grade A")
elif(total > 75):
    print("Grade B")
elif(total > 50):
    print("Grade C")
else:
    print("Grade D")

O/P:
Enter maths marks : 35
Enter science marks : 35
Enter english marks : 35
35.0
Grade D

